        Wayne R. Wilson
    


Staff Writer

Feb 5, 2017













































Wayne R. Wilson



































Wayne R. Wilson, 81, of Lititz, PA went home to be with the Lord on January 26, 2017. He was born in Wilkes Barre, PA. He was the son of the late Edward and Elizabeth Wilson. He was the loving husband of Marian Margaret Wilson (Gobla). They were married for 58 years. Surviving in addition to his wife are three sons and one daughter; Glenn Wilson married to Debbie Wilson, Dwayne Wilson married to Carol Wilson, Karl Wilson married to Sue Wilson, and Nancy Swahl married to Scott Swahl. He was the loving grandfather of 10 grandchildren and 4 great-grandchildren. He was a fan of both Penn State football and the Cleveland Indians. He enjoyed anything to do with automobiles. Especially sprint car racing. He also enjoyed reading and spending time with his grandchildren.Family and friends will be received from 1:30 to 2:30PM, Saturday, February 11, 2017, at Lancaster Evangelical Free Church, 419 Pierson Rd., Lititz, PA 17543. The Memorial Service will begin at 2:30pm. Interment will be at Witness Park following the Memorial Service. Donations in Wayne's memory may be made to Hospice and Community Care, PO Box 4125, Lancaster, PA 17604. To leave the family an online condolence, please visit: SnyderFuneralHome.com














































        

        
        Charles F. Snyder Jr. Funeral Home & Crematory



