Wayne R. Wilson




Wayne Wilson is an affiliate expert in the Lake Oswego, Oregon office of The Bates Group, where he uses his extensive background in the retail brokerage securities industry to consult and provide expert witness testimony on complex financial matters involving annuities and insurance products, mutual funds, options, account performance and analysis, asset allocation, employment issues, compliance and supervision, branch office administration, and sales practices. Mr. Wilson is based in Seattle, Washington.
Before joining the Bates Group, Mr. Wilson was an expert consultant and testimony witness with LECG and Bates Private Capital Incorporated, a firm that provided litigation consulting, financial analysis, market trend research, and expert witness testimony for securities and other financial-related matters.
Mr. Wilson has over twenty years of experience managing complex retail and institutional sales and operations with US Bancorp Piper Jaffray and US Bancorp Investments having served as senior managing director where he was responsible for branch management, supervision, and compliance. As president of US Bancorp Securities, Mr. Wilson managed over 750 employees including discount brokerage services, a mutual fund and annuity sales force and a full-service brokerage division.






